{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":332133,"duration_api_ms":317056,"ttft_ms":10910,"ttft_stream_ms":6037,"time_to_request_ms":1490,"num_turns":8,"result":"I've read the fixture and the four relevant skill references (provenance, the design-system workflow, the game-designer agent, and the GDD template). Below is the draft GDD as text only — no files written. Per the source contract, fixture content is treated as **project fact**, the MDA/SDT/Flow frameworks are used as **design lenses (not empirical proof)**, and every number is a **proposal** flagged for playtest validation.\n\n---\n\n# Lantern Heat System\n\n> **Status:** Draft (proposal — not reviewed)\n> **Implements Pillars:** Readable Risk (primary), Earned Mastery (primary), A Fragile Home Worth Saving (secondary)\n> **Target Aesthetics (MDA, used as a design lens):** Sensation, Challenge, Discovery, Submission\n\n## Summary\n\nThe lantern is the player's only source of light and the expedition's main source of danger. While lit it accumulates **heat** from 0→100. Heat buys visibility (farther navigation-marker reveal) but, above a floor, attracts storms. The player **vents** to shed heat, accepting a temporary loss of sight. At 100 the lantern **overheats**: it goes dark for a fixed duration and cannot be controlled. Discoveries enabled by the lantern become permanent **route knowledge** at home — never character power.\n\n> **Quick reference** — Layer: `Core` · Priority: `MVP` · Key deps: Input, World/Clock, Discovery, Storm, Home/Progression, HUD, VFX/Audio\n\n## Player Fantasy\n\nThe player is a **keeper** tending a flame that is simultaneously their lifeline and their greatest threat. The fantasy is *competent stewardship under pressure*: pushing the light a little farther to find the next marker, feeling the heat build, then choosing the right moment to vent — knowing each vent blinds them for a beat. Mastery reads as rhythm: the novice overheats or vents too late; the expert rides the Strained band deliberately, reading weather and distance, and comes home with a richer map.\n\nThis serves **Readable Risk** (the heat value and its consequences are legible before they bite), **Earned Mastery** (skilled heat/vent cycling yields more discoveries than passive play), and **A Fragile Home Worth Saving** (the lantern *is* the home; letting it overheat is a failure of care, not just a stat loss).\n\n*Reference feel (proposal, not a target to copy):* the oxygen/clock tension of a short-range diving expedition, crossed with a generator that can run away from its operator. Anti-reference: a meter that fills silently and punishes without warning.\n\n## Detailed Design\n\n### Core Rules\n\n1. The lantern has one scalar state variable, **heat**, bounded `[0, 100]`. It can never exceed 100 (hard clamp) and can never go below 0.\n2. While the expedition is active and the lantern is **lit**, heat changes every tick per **Formula 1 (Heat update)**.\n3. The player has two moment-to-moment inputs on the lantern:\n   - **Stoke** — raises the heat-generation rate (mapped to `load_factor`). Pushing heat up reveals farther markers but moves toward overheat and storm attraction.\n   - **Vent (held)** — removes heat at `vent_rate` and, for the duration held, multiplies current visibility by `vent_visibility_multiplier` (< 1). Venting always costs visibility, even at heat 0.\n4. **Visibility** (current reveal radius) is a pure function of heat and vent state (**Formula 2**).\n5. **Storm attraction** is zero below `storm_pull_floor` and rises with heat above it (**Formula 3**). The lantern emits `storm_spawn_rate` to the Storm system.\n6. When heat reaches 100, the lantern enters **Overheat** for `OverheatDuration` seconds. During Overheat: the lantern is dark (visibility = `overheat_visibility_radius`), all stoke/vent input is ignored, and the lantern's storm pull is suppressed (ambient weather still applies).\n7. When Overheat expires, the lantern returns to **Lit-Stable** at a cool baseline heat (proposal: 0; flagged open).\n8. Reaching **Home** ends the expedition: heat resets to 0, state returns to Lit-Stable, in-flight storms are cleared (home is safe harbor), and every marker illuminated during the expedition is handed to Progression as a **route-knowledge candidate** — no character stat or power is increased by this system (fixture-locked).\n\n### States and Transitions\n\n| State | Entry Condition | Exit Condition | Behavior |\n|-------|----------------|----------------|----------|\n| **Lit-Stable** | Expedition start; or heat falls below `StrainThreshold`; or Overheat expires | heat ≥ `StrainThreshold`; or heat → 100 | Normal heat rise; visibility per Formula 2; storm pull active above floor |\n| **Lit-Strained** | heat crosses `StrainThreshold` upward | heat drops below `StrainThreshold`; or heat → 100 | Same formulas; escalating warning feedback; full storm-pull slope in effect |\n| **Overheat** | heat reaches 100 | `OverheatDuration` elapses; or Home reached | Dark lantern (visibility = `overheat_visibility_radius`); input locked; lantern storm pull suppressed |\n\nA **Vent** is modeled as a held input modifier on heat rate and visibility, not as a separate top-level state, so it can coexist with Lit-Stable or Lit-Strained. It cannot coexist with Overheat (input ignored).\n\n### Interactions with Other Systems (summary — see Dependencies for direction)\n\n- **Discovery** consumes `visibility_radius`; it owns marker reveal and short-term memory. Heat never grants discoveries directly — only the radius that enables them.\n- **Storm** consumes `storm_spawn_rate`; it owns spawn, movement, and impact.\n- **Home/Progression** consumes the expedition's discovered-marker set on Home arrival and converts to route knowledge.\n\n## Formulas\n\nAll constants are **proposals**. Ranges are safe-design ranges, not validated balance.\n\n### Formula 1 — Heat update\n\n```\nheat_next = clamp(heat + heat_rate * dt_clamped, 0, HEAT_MAX)\nheat_rate = (base_heat_rate * load_factor) - vent_rate_active - passive_cool_rate\nvent_rate_active = vent_rate if (venting AND state in {Lit-Stable, Lit-Strained}) else 0\ndt_clamped = min(dt, MAX_DT)\n```\n\n| Variable | Type | Range | Source | Description |\n|----------|------|-------|--------|-------------|\n| heat | float | 0–100 | state | Current lantern heat |\n| HEAT_MAX | const int | 100 (fixed) | fixture | Hard ceiling; never exceeded |\n| base_heat_rate | float | 0.5–5.0 /s (proposal 1.5) | tuning | Heat gained per second at `load_factor`=1 |\n| load_factor | float | 0.0–2.0 (proposal idle 1.0) | runtime | Stoke multiplier; 0 = damped, 2 = max stoke |\n| vent_rate | float | 5–25 /s (proposal 12) | tuning | Heat removed per second while venting |\n| passive_cool_rate | float | 0–1.0 /s (proposal 0.2) | tuning | Slow ambient cooling |\n| MAX_DT | float | 0.05–0.1 s (proposal 0.1) | tuning | Per-tick dt clamp to prevent tunneling |\n\n**Output range:** heat ∈ [0, 100]. **Extreme:** any result ≥100 clamps to 100 and forces the Overheat transition; any result ≤0 clamps to 0.\n**Worked example (proposal):** idle lit (load 1.0), no vent → heat_rate = 1.5 − 0 − 0.2 = +1.3/s; from heat=20, after 10s → heat≈33.\n\n### Formula 2 — Visibility radius\n\n```\nvent_visibility_factor = vent_visibility_multiplier if venting else 1.0\nvisibility_radius = (min_radius + (max_radius - min_radius) * (heat / HEAT_MAX)^visibility_exponent) * vent_visibility_factor\nif state == Overheat: visibility_radius = overheat_visibility_radius\n```\n\n| Variable | Type | Range | Source | Description |\n|----------|------|-------|--------|-------------|\n| min_radius | float | 4–15 m (proposal 8) | tuning | Reveal radius at heat 0 |\n| max_radius | float | 40–80 m (proposal 60) | tuning | Reveal radius at heat 100, not venting |\n| visibility_exponent | float | 0.5–1.5 (proposal 0.7) | tuning | Curve shape; <1 = front-loaded (readable early) |\n| vent_visibility_multiplier | float | 0.1–0.6 (proposal 0.35) | tuning | Visibility fraction while venting |\n| overheat_visibility_radius | float | 2–6 m (proposal 4) | tuning | Near-dark perception during Overheat |\n\n**Output range:** visibility_radius ∈ [overheat_visibility_radius, max_radius] (proposal ~4–60 m).\n**Worked example (proposal):** heat=60, not venting → 8 + 52·(0.6)^0.7 ≈ 44 m; venting → ≈ 15 m.\n\n### Formula 3 — Storm attraction\n\n```\nstorm_pull = storm_pull_rate * max(0, heat - storm_pull_floor)\nif state == Overheat: storm_pull = 0\nstorm_spawn_rate = base_storm_rate + storm_pull      // emitted to Storm system\n```\n\n| Variable | Type | Range | Source | Description |\n|----------|------|-------|--------|-------------|\n| storm_pull_floor | float | 20–70 (proposal 40) | tuning | Heat below which the lantern attracts no storms |\n| storm_pull_rate | float | 0.02–0.15 storms/min/heat (proposal 0.06) | tuning | Slope of attraction above the floor |\n| base_storm_rate | float | 0–1.5 /min (proposal 0.5) | tuning (owned w/ Storm GDD) | Ambient weather frequency |\n\n**Output range:** storm_spawn_rate ∈ [base_storm_rate, base_storm_rate + storm_pull_rate·100] (proposal ~0.5–6.5 /min at extremes).\n**Worked example (proposal):** heat=60 → pull = 0.06·20 = 1.2 /min → spawn_rate ≈ 1.7 /min.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n| Scenario | Resolution | Rationale |\n|----------|-----------|-----------|\n| Heat reaches 100 on a tick where **vent is held** | Overheat triggers; vent input is then ignored. Venting is not a \"save\" once 100 is reached. | Reaching 100 is a discrete failure; venting must happen *before*. |\n| **Venting at heat = 0** | Heat clamps at 0; visibility is still reduced to `vent_visibility_multiplier` for the duration. | Venting always costs sight, so it can't be spammed for free. |\n| `StrainThreshold` and `storm_pull_floor` crossed on the same tick | Both are independent predicates on heat; both take effect that tick. No tiebreak needed. | Thresholds don't compete. |\n| **Overheat onset while storms are inbound** | In-flight storms continue; lantern pull suppressed (spawn_rate = base only). | Lantern is dark and can't attract, but weather persists — Overheat is punishing via blindness + incoming weather. |\n| **Reaching Home during Overheat** | Expedition ends; heat→0; state→Lit-Stable; in-flight storms cleared. | Home is safe harbor; state never persists across expeditions. |\n| **dt spike** (stutter / unpause) | `dt_clamped` caps the step; heat cannot tunnel past 100 without the Overheat transition firing. | Determinism of the 100→Overheat event. |\n| heat exactly == `StrainThreshold` | Strained is active for heat ≥ threshold (inclusive). | Removes flicker at the boundary. |\n| Marker **revealed, then** vent shrinks radius below its distance | Marker stays \"discovered\" (Discovery-owned short-term memory); only its *current illumination* changes. | Heat emits radius only; it does not own marker persistence. |\n| **Stoke during Overheat** | Input ignored until `OverheatDuration` elapses. | Overheat is a locked state. |\n| Net heat rate negative (heavy vent + cold) | Heat clamps at 0; no negative heat, no debt. | Single bounded scalar. |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| System | Direction | Nature of dependency |\n|--------|-----------|---------------------|\n| Input/Controls | Heat ← Input | Receives vent (held) and stoke (analog or discrete) intents |\n| World / Expedition Clock | Heat ← World | Receives `dt` and expedition start/end events |\n| World / Environment | Heat ← World (optional) | May receive an environment modifier to `passive_cool_rate` (wind/rain) — **open**, confirm with World GDD |\n| Discovery | Discovery ← Heat | Heat emits `visibility_radius`; Discovery owns reveal + short-term memory |\n| Storm | Storm ← Heat | Heat emits `storm_spawn_rate`; Storm owns spawn, movement, impact |\n| Home / Progression | Progression ← Heat (indirect) | On Home arrival, illuminated markers convert to **route knowledge** — never character power (fixture-locked) |\n| HUD | HUD ← Heat | Receives heat value, state, strain/overheat events |\n| VFX / Audio | VFX/Audio ← Heat | Receives heat level and state-change events for feedback |\n\nHard dependencies (system cannot function without them): Input, World/Clock, Discovery, Storm. Soft dependencies: Environment modifier, HUD, VFX/Audio.\n\n## Tuning Knobs\n\nCategories per the feel/curve/gate model (used as a balancing heuristic, not a research claim).\n\n| Parameter | Category | Proposal | Safe range | Effect of increase | Effect of decrease |\n|-----------|----------|----------|-----------|--------------------|--------------------|\n| base_heat_rate | Feel | 1.5/s | 0.5–5 | Faster time-to-overheat; more vent cycles | Safer idle; slower loop |\n| load_factor max | Feel | 2.0 | 1.5–3 | Bigger stoke payoff/risk | Flatter stoke curve |\n| vent_rate | Feel | 12/s | 5–25 | Faster recovery; shorter blind windows | Longer blind windows; harder |\n| passive_cool_rate | Feel | 0.2/s | 0–1 | Idle drifts cooler | Idle drifts hotter (matches fixture wording) |\n| OverheatDuration | Feel/Gate | 8 s | 4–15 | Harsher punishment | Slap on the wrist |\n| min_radius / max_radius | Curve | 8 / 60 m | 4–15 / 40–80 | More/fewer markers reachable | — |\n| visibility_exponent | Curve | 0.7 | 0.5–1.5 | Front-loads early visibility | Back-loads to high heat |\n| vent_visibility_multiplier | Curve | 0.35 | 0.1–0.6 | Venting less blinding | Venting more punishing |\n| storm_pull_floor | Curve/Gate | 40 | 20–70 | Larger safe-heat band | Storms start earlier |\n| storm_pull_rate | Curve | 0.06 | 0.02–0.15 | Heat escalates storms faster | Storms mostly ambient |\n| StrainThreshold | Gate | 60 | 45–85 | Shorter strain band | Longer strain band |\n| HEAT_MAX | (locked) | 100 | fixed | fixture-locked | fixture-locked |\n| base_storm_rate | Gate | 0.5/min | 0–1.5 | Co-owned with Storm GDD | — |\n\n**Proposed feel target (to validate in playtest, not a fact):** ~4–8 deliberate stoke→vent cycles per 10–15 min expedition. All defaults above are illustrative and must be replaced by measured values.\n\n## Feedback Requirements\n\n| Event | Visual | Audio | Haptic (if supported) | Priority |\n|-------|--------|-------|----------------------|----------|\n| Heat rising | Gauge fill; lantern brightens; color warm→orange | Low lantern hum rising in pitch | — | High |\n| Enter Lit-Strained | Red glow bleed; warm vignette; marker halos brighten | Heat-up hiss; subtle alarm bed | Slow pulse | High |\n| Vent (held) | Steam/particle plume; screen dims to multiplier | Continuous vent rush/hiss | Light constant | High |\n| Reach 100 → Overheat | Lamp guts out; sparks; emergency low-light | Heavy thud; crackle; alarm sting | Hard bump | Critical |\n| Overheat recovery | Relight flare; color returns | Reignition whoosh | Tap | Medium |\n| Storm pulled inbound (crosses floor) | Distant storm cue on horizon | Wind swell / thunder | — | Medium |\n| Reach Home | Warm settle glow; discoveries \"lock in\" | Warm chord; storm fade | Soft pulse | Medium |\n\nAll feedback must reflect state within one frame; the 100→Overheat event must read unmistakably (the failure must be *readable*, per pillar).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (Given-When-Then)\n\n1. **GIVEN** lantern Lit-Stable at heat 20 and idle, **WHEN** one second elapses, **THEN** heat increases by `base_heat_rate − passive_cool_rate` (within float tolerance) and `visibility_radius` updates per Formula 2.\n2. **GIVEN** heat ≥ 99.5 and rising, **WHEN** a tick brings heat to ≥100, **THEN** state transitions to Overheat, `visibility_radius` becomes `overheat_visibility_radius`, and `storm_spawn_rate` returns to `base_storm_rate` (lantern pull suppressed).\n3. **GIVEN** heat 50 and vent held, **WHEN** 3 seconds pass, **THEN** heat decreases by `vent_rate·3` (clamped at 0) **and** `visibility_radius` is multiplied by `vent_visibility_multiplier` for the duration.\n4. **GIVEN** heat 0 and vent held, **WHEN** the player keeps venting, **THEN** heat stays at 0 **and** visibility is still reduced to `vent_visibility_multiplier` (venting has a cost at zero).\n5. **GIVEN** heat < `storm_pull_floor`, **WHEN** heat is queried, **THEN** `storm_pull` = 0 (low-heat play attracts no storms beyond ambient).\n6. **GIVEN** heat rising through `StrainThreshold`, **WHEN** heat first reaches the threshold, **THEN** Strained feedback activates within one frame and persists while heat ≥ threshold.\n7. **GIVEN** state = Overheat, **WHEN** the player presses stoke or vent, **THEN** the input is ignored until `OverheatDuration` elapses.\n8. **GIVEN** state = Overheat, **WHEN** `OverheatDuration` elapses, **THEN** state returns to Lit-Stable and heat is set to the cool baseline (proposal 0; flagged open).\n9. **GIVEN** the player reaches Home, **WHEN** the expedition ends, **THEN** heat resets to 0, state → Lit-Stable, in-flight storms clear, and illuminated markers are handed to Progression as route-knowledge candidates with **no** increase to any character stat/power.\n10. **GIVEN** a frame dt spike (e.g., 0.5 s), **WHEN** heat updates, **THEN** dt is clamped to `MAX_DT`, so heat cannot skip the Overheat transition by tunneling past 100.\n11. **GIVEN** a marker within and a marker beyond `visibility_radius`, **WHEN** venting shrinks the radius below the nearer marker's distance, **THEN** the nearer marker remains \"discovered\" (Discovery-owned) and only its current illumination changes.\n12. **GIVEN** any heat value, **WHEN** sampled, **THEN** heat ∈ [0, 100] (never negative, never >100) across all input combinations.\n\n## Open Questions / Assumptions\n\n- **Storm system** spawn cadence, movement, and impact are assumed owned by a separate Storm GDD; this system only emits `storm_spawn_rate`.\n- **Home/Progression** conversion rules (what counts as \"discovered,\" how route knowledge scales) assumed owned by a Progression GDD.\n- Does the **environment** (wind/rain) modify `passive_cool_rate`? Proposed as an optional input — confirm with World GDD.\n- Is **stoke** analog (continuous `load_factor`) or discrete tiers (Low/Med/High)? Left open.\n- **Post-Overheat baseline** heat: 0 (proposal) vs. a partial recovery value — open.\n- Target expedition length (10–15 min, fixture) should drive the vent-cycle frequency target; needs playtest measurement before any default is treated as balanced.\n\n---\n\n## Sources Applied\n\n- **`verification/fixtures/system-context.md`** — project facts: walking-lighthouse setting, 10–15 min expeditions, the three pillars, and the fixture-locked heat/overheat/home-conversion behavior.\n- **`references/provenance.md`** — source-contract / authority order applied (project fact > vendored upstream > primary > labelled proposal); basis for marking all numerics as proposals.\n- **`references/upstream-workflow-design-system.md`** — system-GDD authoring workflow, required sections, and the completion-steering formats used for Formulas (variable tables + output ranges + worked examples), Edge Cases (condition → resolution → rationale), and Acceptance Criteria (Given-When-Then).\n- **`references/upstream-agent-game-designer.md`** — the 8-section GDD standard; the MDA / Self-Determination / Flow framings used **as design lenses, not as empirical proof** (per the skill's framework-handling guidance); and the feel/curve/gate tuning-knob categorization (used as a balancing heuristic).\n- **`references/upstream-template-game-design-document.md`** — template structures reused: states-and-transitions table, formula variable table, edge-case table, dependencies table, and tuning-knobs table.\n\n**Not loaded:** `references/authoritative-sources.md` — MDA/SDT/Flow are used here only as design framing, not presented as research-backed empirical claims, so the stronger citation bar was not triggered.\n\n---\n\nThis is a draft for your review. No files were written. Notable unresolved risks: (1) every numeric default is unvalidated and needs playtest; (2) Storm, Progression, and World GDDs are assumed to exist and own their side of the interfaces above — if any of those differ, the Dependencies and Formulas 2/3 outputs need re-checking; (3) the vent-cycle cadence target is a feel guess, not a measurement.\n\nI'll exit plan mode since the requested deliverable is complete as text and there are no file changes to make.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"81de9804-3583-45db-b766-8e063b824960","total_cost_usd":0.390003,"usage":{"input_tokens":44454,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":13120,"output_tokens":16847,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6[1M]":{"inputTokens":31561,"outputTokens":14342,"cacheReadInputTokens":12992,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3137106,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":12893,"outputTokens":2505,"cacheReadInputTokens":128,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.07629239999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"80971bca-88f2-4fdd-8ba4-3506b0853e0f"}
